title: Independent isomeric yield ratios of fission products in the epi-cadmium neutron induced fission of 241Pu

x4freetext: Independent isomeric yield ratios of fission products
in the epi-cadmium neutron induced fission of 241Pu

x4codes.hlp: Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Trombay, Mumbai, India
Kyungpook National University, Daegu, Republic of Korea
Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Trombay, Mumbai, India

x4freetext: For short-lived fission products, 100 uL nitrate
solutions of 241Pu (~2 ug) sealed in polypropylene
tube and wrapped separately with 1-mm thick Cd foils
For long-lived fission products, an electrodeposited
target of 241Pu (~25 ug) was covered with 0.075 mm
The samples were wrapped with 1-mm-thick Cd foil.
Targets were irradiated for 10 min at a flux of
1.2 X 10**12 n/cm2/sec for short-lived fission products
Targets were irradiated for 30 min, 60 min and 127 min
